  <syntaxId>xwiki/2.1</syntaxId>
  <hidden>false</hidden>
  <content>== The Car ==

* 1:8 replice of Audi Q2

== Power Supply ==

* 2 seperate energy circuits
* measuring technology and computer
** 6-cell LiPo with 22.2V
** If fully loaded -> operation up to 1 hour
** can be supplied by external power supply with 6-24V
* engine and cruise control
** 2-cell LiPo with 7.4V

== Engine ==

* high torque, brushless motor
* cruise control which allows controlled forward and reverse driving and braking (even at low speeds)
* steering via digital servo motor, also used in model racing
** high actuating power at low operating times

== Lighting ==

* LED lighting
* dimmed beam, turn signals, brake and reversing lights can be controlles via ADTF filters

== Computer ==

* miniTX board
** intel core i5
** 16GB RAM
** 128GB M.2 SSD
** NVIDIA GeForce GTX1050Ti
** 2 Gigabit Ethernet ports
** several USB 3.0 and USB-C
** Bluetooth and WLAN (IEEE 802.11ac)
** additional Arduino micro for battery voltage monitoring

== Sensors ==

* RPLIDAR A2
** front
** >180° fov
** detection range &lt;6m
** 10Hz update rate
* 130° mono video camera
** front
* 80° mono video camera
** back
* Ultrasonic sensors
** 3 back
** 1 left / 1 right
** &lt;4m detection range
** 40Hz update rate
* Wheelspeed sensors
* 9-axis motion tracking sensor for:
** accelerations
** angular rates

== Software ==

* ADTF
** developer license for software available on vehicle computer
** new software releases announced in [[forum>>https://www.audi-autonomous-driving-cup.com/forum/||rel=" noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"]]</content>
</xwikidoc>@


